@page "/Recipes/{id:guid?}/Edit"
@model Plantry.Web.Pages.Recipes.EditModel
@inject Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.ViewFeatures.IFileVersionProvider FileVersionProvider
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = Model.IsCreate ? "New Recipe" : "Edit Recipe";
    // Pure section transforms (normalize / cross-section move / rename-cascade / delete) live in a
    // plain, unit-tested ES module (recipe-sections.js) bridged to window.RecipeSections below. This
    // is NOT a reactive island — Alpine remains the page's reactive layer (ADR-020); the module only
    // hosts the testable pure logic the Alpine handlers call at interaction time.
    var recipeSectionsSrc = FileVersionProvider.AddFileVersionToPath(
        ViewContext.HttpContext.Request.PathBase, "/js/recipe-sections.js");
    // Canonical amount formatter (plantry-jun6) — bridged onto window.IngredientAmount below so
    // fmtQty() cleans row quantities with the same rule Details/Cook render with.
    var ingredientAmountSrc = FileVersionProvider.AddFileVersionToPath(
        ViewContext.HttpContext.Request.PathBase, "/js/ingredient-amount.js");
    // Pure four-field conversion-equation math (plantry-qno9) — bridged onto window.IngredientConversion
    // below so the editor's conversionEcho() derives "so 1 cup ≈ 125 g" from the same rule the unit test
    // pins (__tests__/ingredient-conversion.test.js). Not an island — no reactive runtime here.
    var ingredientConversionSrc = FileVersionProvider.AddFileVersionToPath(
        ViewContext.HttpContext.Request.PathBase, "/js/ingredient-conversion.js");
}

@*
    Recipe editor — J6 (create) and J7 (edit).

    Alpine x-data carries:
      - tags[]         : array of {id, name} objects — selected tag chips
      - tagQuery       : the current filter text in the tag input
      - tagDropOpen    : whether the tag picker dropdown is visible
      - tagOptions[]   : [{id, name}] — all active household tags (server-serialised, filter client-side)
      - filteredTagOptions() : tagOptions filtered by tagQuery, excluding already-selected tags
      - addTagFromOption(opt) : adds a tag chip from a dropdown selection
      - servings       : current servings value (mirrors the input, for scale-offer visibility)
      - origServings   : the original servings (populated from server; 0 for create)
      - hasIngredients : whether the recipe has pre-existing ingredients (enables scale offer)
      - scaleMode      : "Keep" | "Proportional"
      - rows[]         : committed ingredient rows — each has { _id, ordinal, productId, productName, qty,
                          unitId, groupHeading, isUntracked, newStapleName, newStapleUnit,
                          needsConversion, conversionFactor, conversionFromUnitId, conversionToUnitId }
                          _id is a stable client id (survives reorder); ordinal is the canonical
                          post/render position, reassigned by recipe-sections.js on every mutation.
      - unitCodes{}    : unitId → unit-code map, for rendering read-only row summaries
      - sections()     : rows clustered into display sections (Ungrouped first, then headings first-seen)
      - removeRow(row) : removes the given row, then re-normalises section order + ordinals
      - onDragStart(row,ev), onDragOver(section,ev), onDragEnd() : live-shift drag with cross-section
                          GroupHeading reassignment (delegates to window.RecipeSections.placeRow)
      - renameSection / deleteSection : heading rename cascade + section delete → Ungrouped

    Ingredient editing uses an add/edit *sheet* (modal) rather than inline rows. Committed rows
    render read-only (rowSummary(row)); the sheet edits a working copy:
      - sheetOpen      : whether the sheet is shown (mounted via x-if)
      - editingIdx     : null while adding; the row index while editing
      - draft{}        : working copy of the ingredient being added/edited (same shape as a row)
      - openAdd() / openEdit(idx) / closeSheet() / saveSheet() : sheet lifecycle. saveSheet pushes
                          a new row or splices the edited one back into rows[].

    Hidden inputs are generated from rows[] by x-bind:value, so the server binds
    Input.Lines[n].PropertyName via model binding. Per ADR-005, Alpine owns the unsaved draft state;
    the form-binding hidden inputs are the source of truth that posts and mirror rows[].
*@

@*
    Inline-create staple mode (C12): in the add/edit sheet, when the product search yields no match
    the user clicks "Create as staple" to switch the draft from product-pick mode to new-staple mode.
    The search input becomes the staple name and a unit select appears. Surfaced by draft.newStapleName !== null.
*@

@{
    // Build the tags initial state as [{id, name}] objects and the tag options as [{id, name}] for filtering.
    // JsonSerializer.Serialize without Html.Raw — the JSON is emitted as a safe JavaScript literal via
    // Alpine's x-data attribute; Razor HTML-encodes the attribute value, so the string must NOT be
    // double-encoded via Html.Raw. Alpine reads the attribute value before HTML entity decoding and the
    // browser decodes entities in attribute values, so &quot; / &amp; round-trip correctly.
    var tagsInitJson = System.Text.Json.JsonSerializer.Serialize(
        Model.Input.TagIds
            .Zip(Model.Input.TagNames, (id, name) => new { id = id.ToString(), name })
            .ToList());
    var tagOptionsJson = System.Text.Json.JsonSerializer.Serialize(
        Model.TagOptions
            .Select(o => new { id = o.Value, name = o.Text })
            .ToList());

    // ── Combined editor rows (plantry-fqb0.3) ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    // Ingredient AND inclusion lines share one rows[] array with a `kind` discriminator, so inclusions
    // render in ordinal position, drag/reorder, and interleave with ingredient ordinals for free
    // (recipe-sections.js only touches _id/ordinal/groupHeading). Built ordered by the shared ordinal so
    // the first synchronous render matches the stored order; normalizeRows re-runs on the first mutation.
    var _editorRows = new List<(int Ordinal, object Row)>();
    var _rid = 0;
    foreach (var l in Model.Input.Lines)
    {
        // plantry-obg3: seed each row's stock/default unit from the PRODUCT's real default (hydrated on
        // GET into l.DefaultUnitId), so the landed-row conversion heading shows the actual unit code
        // before hydration and the client same-unit short-circuit is correct. Fall back to
        // ConversionToUnitId for a NeedsConversion POST bounce, where OnPostAsync sets it to the needed
        // target (product default) unit and l.DefaultUnitId is not posted back.
        var seedDefaultUnitId = l.DefaultUnitId != Guid.Empty ? l.DefaultUnitId : l.ConversionToUnitId;
        _editorRows.Add((l.Ordinal, new
        {
            _id = _rid++,
            kind = "ingredient",
            ordinal = l.Ordinal,
            productId = l.ProductId?.ToString() ?? "",
            productName = l.ProductName ?? "",
            // Seed the qty already cleaned (plantry-jun6) so a scaled decimal (500.000) doesn't render "500.000 g".
            qty = l.Quantity.HasValue ? IngredientAmount.Format(l.Quantity.Value) : "",
            unitId = l.UnitId?.ToString() ?? "",
            defaultUnitId = seedDefaultUnitId.ToString(),
            defaultUnitCode = seedDefaultUnitId != Guid.Empty
                ? (Model.UnitOptions.FirstOrDefault(u => u.Value == seedDefaultUnitId.ToString())?.Text ?? "")
                : "",
            groupHeading = l.GroupHeading ?? "",
            isUntracked = l.IsUntracked,
            // Round-trip the inline-create fields from the posted line (plantry-5oek Defect 2). On a
            // failed-save bounce (AuthorRecipeResult.Invalid / NeedsConversion) an inline-create row must
            // re-seed with its typed name/unit/category/parent intact — hard-coding these to null/false/""
            // produced a blank "ghost" row (rowSummary read an empty productName, rowNeedsQtyUnit skipped
            // it). An empty NewStapleName maps back to null, NOT "", because Alpine detects a create row via
            // `newStapleName !== null`. On the GET path (existing recipe) every field below is default, so
            // the serialised JSON is byte-identical to the previous hard-coded values — only a POST bounce
            // re-render now carries the real inline-create state.
            newStapleName = string.IsNullOrEmpty(l.NewStapleName) ? (string?)null : l.NewStapleName,
            newStapleUnit = l.NewStapleDefaultUnitId?.ToString() ?? "",
            newIsTracked = l.NewIsTracked,
            newGroupId = l.NewGroupId ?? "",
            newGroupName = l.NewGroupName ?? "",
            newStapleCategoryId = l.NewStapleCategoryId?.ToString() ?? "",
            needsConversion = l.NeedsConversion,
            conversionFactor = l.ConversionFactor?.ToString() ?? "",
            conversionFromUnitId = l.ConversionFromUnitId.ToString(),
            conversionToUnitId = l.ConversionToUnitId.ToString(),
            convLeftAmount = l.ConversionLeftAmount?.ToString() ?? "",
            convLeftUnitId = l.ConversionLeftUnitId?.ToString() ?? "",
            convRightAmount = l.ConversionRightAmount?.ToString() ?? "",
            convRightUnitId = l.ConversionRightUnitId?.ToString() ?? "",
            convFor = "",
            stockUnits = new object[0],
            recipeUnits = new object[0],
            // plantry-obg3: set true by the CheckConversion fetch when the product's default/stock unit cannot
            // be resolved — the row then shows an explicit message instead of the option-less equation.
            // plantry-dnbe: also seeded true here on a NeedsConversion POST bounce, where OnPostAsync resolves
            // the needed conversion axes against the household unit list — so the FIRST render after a save
            // bounce is already correct, without relying on the client's maybeHydrateRowConversion fetch. On
            // the GET path l.DefaultUnitMissing is default false, keeping the serialised row JSON identical.
            defaultUnitMissing = l.DefaultUnitMissing,
            // plantry-hhy2: RIGHT/recipe-axis counterpart — set true when the chosen recipe-line unit cannot
            // be resolved. Shows recipe-axis copy instead of the stock-unit-specific message.
            recipeUnitMissing = l.RecipeUnitMissing,
        }));
    }
    foreach (var inc in Model.Input.Inclusions)
    {
        _editorRows.Add((inc.Ordinal, new
        {
            _id = _rid++,
            kind = "inclusion",
            ordinal = inc.Ordinal,
            groupHeading = inc.GroupHeading ?? "",
            subRecipeId = inc.SubRecipeId.ToString(),
            subName = inc.SubName ?? "",
            servings = inc.Servings,
            subDefaultServings = inc.SubDefaultServings <= 0 ? 1 : inc.SubDefaultServings,
        }));
    }
    var editorRowsJson = System.Text.Json.JsonSerializer.Serialize(
        _editorRows.OrderBy(r => r.Ordinal).Select(r => r.Row).ToList());
    var editorRowCount = _editorRows.Count;

    // D13 fixed-mode warning: includer names for the recipe being edited.
    var includedByNamesJson = System.Text.Json.JsonSerializer.Serialize(Model.IncludedByNames);
}

<page-header title="@(Model.IsCreate ? "New Recipe" : "Edit Recipe")"
             subtitle="@(Model.IsCreate ? "Add a recipe by hand, or import one from a link." : "Update this recipe's details, ingredients, and steps.")" />

<div id="recipe-editor"
     x-data="{
         tags: @tagsInitJson,
         tagQuery: '',
         tagDropOpen: false,
         tagOptions: @tagOptionsJson,
         filteredTagOptions() {
             const q = this.tagQuery.trim().toLowerCase();
             return this.tagOptions.filter(o =>
                 !this.tags.some(t => t.id === o.id) &&
                 (!q || o.name.toLowerCase().includes(q)));
         },
         addTagFromOption(opt) {
             if (!this.tags.some(t => t.id === opt.id))
                 this.tags.push({ id: opt.id, name: opt.name });
             this.tagQuery = '';
             this.tagDropOpen = false;
             this.$nextTick(() => this.$refs.tagInput.focus());
         },
         // AI tag suggestions (plantry-qll2.2) — create-moment only. Fires ONCE per create, the first
         // time an ingredient exists (not on every save; the contradiction nudge covers edits). The
         // server gate check + LLM call live behind SuggestTags; a suggestion NEVER auto-applies —
         // acceptSuggestion runs only on a tap.
         isCreate: @(Model.IsCreate ? "true" : "false"),
         tagSuggestFetched: false,
         tagSuggestDismissed: false,
         tagSuggestions: [],   // [{ name, category, existingTagId, isNew }]
         newTags: [],          // accepted new-tag chips (minted on save): [{ name, category }]
         async maybeSuggestTags() {
             if (!this.isCreate || this.tagSuggestFetched || this.tagSuggestDismissed) return;
             const productIds = this.rows.map(r => r.productId).filter(id => id);
             if (productIds.length === 0) return;
             this.tagSuggestFetched = true; // fire-once latch, set before await so re-entry is a no-op
             try {
                 const params = productIds.map(id => 'productIds=' + encodeURIComponent(id)).join('&');
                 const url = `@Url.Page("./Edit", "SuggestTags")&${params}`;
                 const res = await fetch(url, { headers: { 'Accept': 'application/json' } });
                 if (!res.ok) return;
                 const data = await res.json();
                 // Drop any suggestion already applied (existing tag already a chip, or new tag already accepted).
                 this.tagSuggestions = (data.suggestions || []).filter(s =>
                     s.isNew
                         ? !this.newTags.some(t => t.name.toLowerCase() === s.name.toLowerCase())
                         : !this.tags.some(t => t.id === s.existingTagId));
             } catch (e) { /* soft-fail: no chips, editor unchanged */ }
         },
         acceptSuggestion(sug) {
             if (sug.isNew) {
                 if (!this.newTags.some(t => t.name.toLowerCase() === sug.name.toLowerCase()))
                     this.newTags.push({ name: sug.name, category: sug.category || '' });
             } else {
                 this.addTagFromOption({ id: sug.existingTagId, name: sug.name });
             }
             this.tagSuggestions = this.tagSuggestions.filter(s => s !== sug);
         },
         removeNewTag(i) { this.newTags.splice(i, 1); },
         dismissSuggestions() { this.tagSuggestDismissed = true; this.tagSuggestions = []; },
         servings: @Model.Input.DefaultServings,
         origServings: @Model.OriginalServings,
         hasIngredients: @(Model.HasExistingIngredients ? "true" : "false"),
         scaleMode: '@Model.Input.ScaleMode.ToString()',
         rows: @editorRowsJson,
         _nextId: @editorRowCount,
         unitCodes: @System.Text.Json.JsonSerializer.Serialize(Model.UnitOptions.ToDictionary(u => u.Value, u => u.Text)),

         // ── Inclusions (plantry-fqb0.3) ────────────────────────────────────────────
         // Inclusion rows live in the shared rows[] array (kind === 'inclusion'). These filtered views feed
         // the two contiguous-index hidden-input loops so ingredients post Input.Lines[i] and inclusions
         // post Input.Inclusions[j], both carrying the shared `ordinal`.
         ingredientRows() { return this.rows.filter(r => r.kind !== 'inclusion'); },
         inclusionRows() { return this.rows.filter(r => r.kind === 'inclusion'); },
         // D13 fixed-mode warning data (who includes THIS recipe).
         includedByCount: @Model.IncludedByCount,
         includedByNames: @includedByNamesJson,
         includedByLabel() {
             const n = this.includedByCount;
             const names = (this.includedByNames || []).slice(0, 3).join(', ');
             const more = this.includedByNames.length > 3 ? ', …' : '';
             const noun = n === 1 ? 'recipe that includes' : 'recipes that include';
             return n + ' ' + noun + ' this one (' + names + more + ')';
         },
         // Recipe-search 'Include a recipe' affordance (D11). Hits the Recipes-scoped SearchRecipes JSON
         // handler; self is excluded server-side (N4 authoritative at save). Duplicate subs are allowed (D14).
         inclusionSearchOpen: false,
         inclusionQuery: '',
         inclusionResults: [],
         _inclSearchTimer: null,
         openInclusionSearch() {
             this.inclusionSearchOpen = true;
             this.inclusionQuery = '';
             this.inclusionResults = [];
             this.searchInclusions();
             this.$nextTick(() => { if (this.$refs.inclusionInput) this.$refs.inclusionInput.focus(); });
         },
         closeInclusionSearch() { this.inclusionSearchOpen = false; },
         searchInclusions() {
             clearTimeout(this._inclSearchTimer);
             this._inclSearchTimer = setTimeout(async () => {
                 try {
                     const url = `@Url.Page("./Edit", "SearchRecipes")&q=${encodeURIComponent(this.inclusionQuery.trim())}`;
                     const res = await fetch(url, { headers: { 'Accept': 'application/json' } });
                     if (!res.ok) return;
                     const data = await res.json();
                     this.inclusionResults = data.hits || [];
                 } catch (e) { /* soft-fail: no results, editor unchanged */ }
             }, 200);
         },
         addInclusion(hit) {
             const def = Number(hit.defaultServings) || 1;
             this.rows.push({
                 _id: this._nextId++, kind: 'inclusion', ordinal: this.rows.length, groupHeading: '',
                 subRecipeId: hit.id, subName: hit.name, servings: def, subDefaultServings: def,
             });
             this.rows = window.RecipeSections.normalizeRows(this.rows);
             this.inclusionSearchOpen = false;
             this.inclusionQuery = '';
             this.inclusionResults = [];
         },
         // Inclusion row display (D2): 'N servings' title + a '½ batch' fraction hint (batch = servings/subDefault).
         inclusionServingsLabel(row) {
             const s = Number(row.servings);
             if (!s || s <= 0) return '0 servings';
             const n = Number.isInteger(s) ? s : Number(s.toFixed(2));
             return n + (n === 1 ? ' serving' : ' servings');
         },
         batchHint(row) {
             const d = Number(row.subDefaultServings) || 1;
             const s = Number(row.servings);
             if (!s || s <= 0 || d <= 0) return '';
             const b = s / d;
             const glyphs = { '0.25': '¼', '0.5': '½', '0.75': '¾', '0.33': '⅓', '0.67': '⅔' };
             const key = (Math.round(b * 100) / 100).toString();
             if (glyphs[key]) return glyphs[key] + ' batch';
             const clean = Number(b.toFixed(2)).toString();
             return clean + (Number(clean) === 1 ? ' batch' : ' batches');
         },

         // Ingredient sheet (add / edit)
         sheetOpen: false,
         // sheetView: 'search' | 'create' — drives the two-view swap in _ProductSearchCreateSheet
         // (plantry-nb4x).  Recipes currently only uses the search view; plantry-orix wires the
         // create-view path for the tracked-product create on this surface.
         sheetView: 'search',
         // plantry-5oek: inline guard message for the add/edit sheet. Non-empty blocks the commit and
         // renders next to the Quantity field (Model.TrackStock-gated in _ProductSearchCreateSheet).
         // Cleared on qty input, on view swap ($watch below), and on every open/close.
         sheetError: '',
         editingIdx: null,
         draft: {},
         blankDraft() {
             return { _id: null, ordinal: 0, productId: '', productName: '', qty: '', unitId: '',
                 defaultUnitId: '', defaultUnitCode: '',
                 groupHeading: '', isUntracked: false, newStapleName: null, newStapleUnit: '',
                 // recipeUnitPinned (plantry-dtr9): set once the author picks a recipe-line unit in the
                 // create view, so the newStapleUnit→unitId mirror stands down and never overwrites it.
                 recipeUnitPinned: false,
                 newIsTracked: false,
                 newStapleCategoryId: '', newGroupId: '', newGroupName: '',
                 needsConversion: false, conversionFactor: '', conversionFromUnitId: '', conversionToUnitId: '',
                 convLeftAmount: '', convLeftUnitId: '', convRightAmount: '', convRightUnitId: '',
                 convFor: '', stockUnits: [], recipeUnits: [],
                 // plantry-obg3: true when the product's default (stock) unit is unresolvable — the prompt
                 // then shows an explicit human-readable message instead of a blank-unit sentence + an
                 // option-less dropdown.
                 defaultUnitMissing: false,
                 // plantry-hhy2: RIGHT/recipe-axis counterpart — true when the chosen recipe-line unit is
                 // unresolvable. Shows recipe-axis copy instead of the stock-unit-specific message.
                 recipeUnitMissing: false };
         },
         openAdd() { this.editingIdx = null; this.sheetView = 'search'; this.sheetError = ''; this.draft = this.blankDraft(); this.sheetOpen = true; this._syncSearch(''); },
         // editingIdx carries the row's stable _id while editing (null while adding). The shared
         // sheet only tests `editingIdx === null` (add vs edit), so an _id value satisfies it.
         openEdit(row) {
             this.editingIdx = row._id;
             this.sheetError = '';
             // A tracked inline-create row (no productId yet, minted from a typed name) reopens in the
             // CREATE view so its name/unit/category/parent are visible and editable again (plantry-5oek).
             // Product-pick rows and legacy untracked staples keep opening in the search view.
             this.sheetView = (!row.productId && row.newIsTracked === true) ? 'create' : 'search';
             this.draft = JSON.parse(JSON.stringify(row));
             // A reopened row already has a decided recipe-line unit — pin it so the create-view mirror
             // ($watch on draft.newStapleUnit) cannot overwrite it when the draft is (re)assigned (plantry-dtr9).
             this.draft.recipeUnitPinned = true;
             this.sheetOpen = true;
             this._syncSearch(this.draft.productName);
         },
         // The sheet stays mounted (x-show), so the nested searchableSelect inits once. Push the
         // current product label into its search box each time the sheet opens.
         _syncSearch(label) { this.$nextTick(() => window.dispatchEvent(new CustomEvent('sheet-product-set', { detail: label || '' }))); },
         closeSheet() { this.sheetView = 'search'; this.sheetError = ''; this.sheetOpen = false; },
         draftIsEmpty() {
             return !this.draft.productId && !(this.draft.newStapleName && this.draft.newStapleName.trim());
         },
         saveSheet() {
             if (this.draftIsEmpty()) { this.sheetView = 'search'; this.sheetError = ''; this.sheetOpen = false; return; }
             this.sheetError = '';
             // The in-sheet four-field equation (plantry-qno9) is the author's entry point. Clear
             // needsConversion on commit ONLY when the author actually filled a valid equation
             // (rowConvFilled) — then the landed row shows the neutral FILLED confirmation, and the raw
             // equation values still POST via hidden inputs for AuthorRecipe's authoritative re-check.
             // If the author saw the cross-dimension prompt but clicked Add without completing it, leave
             // needsConversion set (plantry-mfoe): the committed row lands showing the MISSING ask
             // immediately, not only after a later save bounce — matching plantry-wq9s's stated intent
             // that MISSING covers the author-skipped-the-sheet-prompt case as well as the server bounce.
             if (this.rowConvFilled(this.draft)) {
                 this.draft.needsConversion = false;
             }
             // When saving from the create view, mark the row as a tracked product create
             // (plantry-orix). The untracked-staple path (C12) is now only used when newIsTracked
             // is false — which is the legacy path kept for backward compatibility in the data model;
             // the create view always mints tracked products (the whole point of plantry-orix).
             // Recipe-line unit (draft.unitId) and product default/stock unit (draft.newStapleUnit) are
             // independent (plantry-dtr9). Fall each back to the other ONLY when one is blank — a value the
             // author chose on either side is never overwritten (criterion 3):
             //   • recipe unit blank    → inherit the product default (matches today's behaviour, now visible)
             //   • product default blank → stock it in the recipe unit (so the mint always has a default unit)
             if (this.sheetView === 'create' && this.draft.newStapleName !== null) {
                 this.draft.newIsTracked = true;
                 if (this.draft.newStapleUnit && !this.draft.unitId) {
                     this.draft.unitId = this.draft.newStapleUnit;
                 } else if (this.draft.unitId && !this.draft.newStapleUnit) {
                     this.draft.newStapleUnit = this.draft.unitId;
                 }
             }
             // plantry-5oek Defect 1 — block a tracked draft that lacks a usable quantity or unit before it
             // commits. A tracked line with no quantity is R5-rejected server-side (Recipes.TrackedRequires-
             // Quantity), which previously bounced to a blank ghost row (Defect 2). Guarding here keeps the
             // sheet open with an inline message so the author fixes it in place. Quantity must be > 0
             // (a 0-qty tracked ingredient is meaningless; this is stricter than the server's non-null R5 —
             // the server is intentionally unchanged). The legacy untracked-staple path (newIsTracked false,
             // blank qty legal per C12/R5) is exempt. Unit is checked too — the create-view block just above
             // falls draft.unitId back to draft.newStapleUnit, so draft.unitId is authoritative here.
             const isTrackedDraft = (!!this.draft.productId && !this.draft.isUntracked) || this.draft.newIsTracked === true;
             if (isTrackedDraft) {
                 const qtyOk = this.draft.qty != null && String(this.draft.qty).trim() !== '' && Number(this.draft.qty) > 0;
                 if (!qtyOk) { this.sheetError = 'Enter a quantity greater than 0 for this tracked product.'; return; }
                 if (!this.draft.unitId) { this.sheetError = 'Choose a unit for this tracked product.'; return; }
             }
             if (this.editingIdx === null) {
                 this.draft._id = this._nextId++;
                 this.rows.push(JSON.parse(JSON.stringify(this.draft)));
             } else {
                 const i = this.rows.findIndex(r => r._id === this.editingIdx);
                 if (i >= 0) this.rows.splice(i, 1, JSON.parse(JSON.stringify(this.draft)));
             }
             // Re-cluster the flat list into canonical section order (ungrouped-first, first-seen)
             // and reassign ordinals so the posted order equals what Details renders.
             this.rows = window.RecipeSections.normalizeRows(this.rows);             this.sheetView = 'search';
             this.sheetOpen = false;
             // Create-moment tag suggestions (plantry-qll2.2): fire once now that an ingredient exists.
             this.maybeSuggestTags();
         },
         unitLabel(id) { return this.unitCodes[id] || ''; },
         // ── Four-field conversion equation (plantry-qno9) ──────────────────────────
         // Looks a unit up in one of the axis lists returned by CheckConversion (each item carries
         // {id, code, factorToBase}). Returns null when absent so callers stay quiet.
         _convUnitMeta(id, list) {
             if (!id || !Array.isArray(list)) return null;
             return list.find(u => u.id === id) || null;
         },
         // Derived echo: translates the entered equation into stock terms, e.g. so 1 cup of Cashews is
         // about 125 g. Returns '' while either amount is incomplete/invalid so nothing is shown
         // mid-typing. Pure client-side courtesy; the server re-check remains authoritative.
         // Shared by the in-sheet prompt (draft) and the landed-row block (row) via _convEchoText.
         _convEchoText(d) {
             if (!d) return '';
             // Read every reactive equation field BEFORE the module guard so Alpine's effect tracking
             // captures them as dependencies even on the first evaluation — plantry-ac23. A server-seeded
             // row (a save bounce, or editing a recipe with a pending gap) renders before the awaited
             // dynamic import bridges window.IngredientConversion (the Scripts section runs after Alpine
             // starts). If the guard short-circuited first, this effect would capture ZERO row deps and
             // freeze the row's tone bindings (:class, saved-note/ask x-show) permanently — so the later
             // inline edit would never live-flip MISSING→FILLED. window is not reactive, so we still bail
             // when the module is absent; the captured deps guarantee a re-run once the author edits.
             const leftAmount = d.convLeftAmount, rightAmount = d.convRightAmount;
             const lu = this._convUnitMeta(d.convLeftUnitId, d.stockUnits);
             const ru = this._convUnitMeta(d.convRightUnitId, d.recipeUnits);
             const stockDefault = this._convUnitMeta(d.defaultUnitId, d.stockUnits);
             const recipeLine = this._convUnitMeta(d.unitId, d.recipeUnits);
             if (!window.IngredientConversion) return '';
             if (!lu || !ru || !stockDefault || !recipeLine) return '';
             const per = window.IngredientConversion.stockPerRecipeUnit({
                 leftAmount, rightAmount,
                 leftFactor: lu.factorToBase, rightFactor: ru.factorToBase,
                 recipeLineFactor: recipeLine.factorToBase, stockDefaultFactor: stockDefault.factorToBase });
             const num = window.IngredientConversion.formatEchoAmount(per);
             if (num === '') return '';
             return `Got it — so 1 ${this.unitLabel(d.unitId)} of ${d.productName} ≈ ${num} ${d.defaultUnitCode}.`;
         },
         conversionEcho() {
             // In-sheet prompt only echoes while the sheet actively asks (draft.needsConversion).
             if (!this.draft || !this.draft.needsConversion) return '';
             return this._convEchoText(this.draft);
         },
         // ── Landed-row conversion block (plantry-wq9s) ─────────────────────────────
         // The block under an ingredient row has two tones, keyed off whether the row's four-field
         // equation is complete — NOT off needsConversion (which the sheet's Add clears on commit).
         //   FILLED   : the author already stated the fact (in the sheet, or via this block) — show a
         //              neutral confirmation with the derived echo + a saved-on-save note, no warning.
         //   MISSING  : needsConversion is set (a save bounced, or the sheet ask was skipped) and no
         //              valid equation yet — show the warning-accented informational ask in the same
         //              voice as the in-sheet prompt, so the blocked save is findable and fixable inline.
         // rowConvFilled reuses the sheet's echo-based validity: a non-empty echo means the equation
         // both parses and bridges, exactly the condition the in-sheet prompt treats as complete.
         rowConversionEcho(row) { return this._convEchoText(row); },
         rowConvFilled(row) { return this.rowConversionEcho(row) !== ''; },
         rowShowConversion(row) { return !!row && (row.needsConversion || this.rowConvFilled(row)); },
         // A landed row carrying needsConversion after a server bounce was rendered without the axis
         // unit lists the four-field editor needs (they are populated live during the sheet check, but
         // server-seeded rows start empty). Lazily fetch them from the same CheckConversion GET used by
         // the sheet — no new server behaviour — and mirror the sheet's one-number prefill. Runs once per
         // row via x-init; a cheap no-op for every non-conversion row.
         async maybeHydrateRowConversion(row) {
             if (!row || !row.needsConversion) return;
             if (row.stockUnits && row.stockUnits.length) return;
             if (!row.productId || !row.unitId) return;
             try {
                 const url = `@Url.Page("./Edit", "CheckConversion")&productId=${encodeURIComponent(row.productId)}&fromUnitId=${encodeURIComponent(row.unitId)}`;
                 const res = await fetch(url, { headers: { 'Accept': 'application/json' } });
                 if (!res.ok) return;
                 const data = await res.json();
                 if (!data.needsConversion) { row.needsConversion = false; return; }
                 // plantry-obg3/hhy2: either axis unit unresolvable — show the axis-appropriate explicit
                 // message instead of the option-less equation (mirrors the in-sheet prompt). Clear the axis
                 // lists. (!! guards older cached responses lacking the recipeUnitMissing field.)
                 if (data.defaultUnitMissing || data.recipeUnitMissing) {
                     row.defaultUnitMissing = !!data.defaultUnitMissing;
                     row.recipeUnitMissing = !!data.recipeUnitMissing;
                     row.stockUnits = [];
                     row.recipeUnits = [];
                     return;
                 }
                 row.defaultUnitMissing = false;
                 row.recipeUnitMissing = false;
                 row.defaultUnitId = data.defaultUnitId || row.defaultUnitId;
                 row.defaultUnitCode = data.defaultUnitCode || row.defaultUnitCode;
                 row.stockUnits = data.stockUnits || [];
                 row.recipeUnits = data.recipeUnits || [];
                 // Only prefill when the author has not already entered amounts (a round-tripped entry
                 // must survive): blank stock amount + 1 recipe unit, same as the sheet.
                 if (row.convLeftAmount === '' && row.convRightAmount === '') {
                     row.convRightAmount = '1';
                     // plantry-dhqm: assign the axis unit ids AFTER the option template x-for has
                     // rendered (see _triggerConversionCheck for the full rationale) so the select
                     // x-model binds to a real option element instead of the first one while the model
                     // holds the stock default.
                     const leftUnitId = row.defaultUnitId, rightUnitId = row.unitId;
                     await this.$nextTick();
                     row.convLeftUnitId = leftUnitId;
                     row.convRightUnitId = rightUnitId;
                 }
             } catch (_) { /* network error — silently ignore, server backstop still highlights the row */ }
         },
         // plantry-429l: a tracked (stock-tracked) ingredient row that is missing a quantity or a unit
         // will be rejected by R5 on save. Flag it in-place so the author sees WHICH row is broken
         // instead of dead-ending on the opaque global save error. Computed reactively so it clears the
         // instant the author supplies the missing value. This flags both a tracked product-pick row
         // (productId set) AND a tracked inline-create row (no productId yet, minted from a typed name —
         // plantry-5oek): if a blank-qty create line ever lands on a bounce re-render (JS off, stale
         // client), the row surfaces this row-scoped warning instead of a blank ghost. Inclusions and
         // untracked staples are excluded.
         rowNeedsQtyUnit(row) {
             const isTracked = (!row.isUntracked && !!row.productId) || (row.newIsTracked === true && !!row.newStapleName);
             return isTracked && (!row.qty || !row.unitId);
         },
         // Canonical amount rendering (plantry-jun6) — mirrors C# IngredientAmount.Format via the
         // ingredient-amount.js twin bridged onto window.IngredientAmount below. Cleans a raw qty the
         // author may have typed in the sheet (e.g. 500.000) for the read-only row summary. Falls back
         // to the raw value if the module has not resolved yet; seeded rows are already server-cleaned.
         fmtQty(qty) {
             return window.IngredientAmount ? window.IngredientAmount.formatAmount(qty) : String(qty);
         },
         rowSummary(row) {
             // Group heading is NO LONGER crammed into the summary — it is the section header now.
             const name = row.newStapleName ? row.newStapleName : row.productName;
             const parts = [];
             if (!row.isUntracked && row.qty) parts.push(this.fmtQty(row.qty) + (this.unitLabel(row.unitId) ? ' ' + this.unitLabel(row.unitId) : ''));
             if (row.isUntracked) parts.push('untracked');
             return parts.length ? name + ' · ' + parts.join(' · ') : name;
         },
         removeRow(row) {
             this.rows = window.RecipeSections.normalizeRows(this.rows.filter(r => r._id !== row._id));         },

         // ── Section model (plantry-vff8) ───────────────────────────────────────────
         _isUngrouped(h) { return h == null || String(h).trim() === ''; },
         // Display sections for render: the ungrouped bucket first (nameless), then each named
         // heading in first-appearance order. Mirrors recipe-sections.js deriveSections but kept
         // inline so the FIRST synchronous render never depends on window.RecipeSections having
         // loaded yet (that module is bridged after Alpine starts; every mutation call below runs
         // at interaction time, when it is guaranteed present).
         sections() {
             const secs = [{ key: '__ungrouped__', heading: '', isUngrouped: true,
                             items: this.rows.filter(r => this._isUngrouped(r.groupHeading)) }];
             const seen = [];
             for (const r of this.rows) {
                 const h = r.groupHeading;
                 if (this._isUngrouped(h) || seen.includes(h)) continue;
                 seen.push(h);
                 secs.push({ key: 'g:' + h, heading: h, isUngrouped: false,
                             items: this.rows.filter(x => x.groupHeading === h) });
             }
             return secs;
         },
         // The nameless Ungrouped header is hidden when it is the only section (a recipe with no
         // headings looks essentially like today); it appears once at least one named section
         // exists. The ungrouped rows themselves always render (header or not).
         showUngroupedHeader() { return this.sections().length > 1; },
         // Distinct existing section names on this recipe — feeds the add/edit sheet's section picker.
         existingSectionHeadings() {
             const seen = [];
             for (const r of this.rows) {
                 if (this._isUngrouped(r.groupHeading) || seen.includes(r.groupHeading)) continue;
                 seen.push(r.groupHeading);
             }
             return seen;
         },
         renameSection(oldHeading, newName) {
             this.rows = window.RecipeSections.renameSection(this.rows, oldHeading, newName);         },
         deleteSection(heading) {
             this.rows = window.RecipeSections.deleteSection(this.rows, heading);         },

         // ── Drag (live-shift, cross-section reassignment) ──────────────────────────
         _dragId: null,
         _dragActive: false,
         onDragStart(row, ev) {
             this._dragId = row._id;
             this._dragActive = true;
             if (ev && ev.dataTransfer) { ev.dataTransfer.effectAllowed = 'move'; ev.dataTransfer.setData('text/plain', String(row._id)); }
         },
         // Live shift: as the pointer moves over a section, reflow the dragged row to the cursor
         // position and (when the section differs) reassign its group — so the editor order tracks
         // the Details render in real time. Mutates rows on dragover, exactly like the flat editor
         // did; the reactive :class keeps the dragged row styled across re-renders.
         onDragOver(section, ev) {
             if (this._dragId === null) return;
             ev.preventDefault();
             const container = ev.currentTarget;
             const rowEls = Array.from(container.querySelectorAll('.ingredient-row'))
                 .filter(el => Number(el.dataset.rowId) !== this._dragId);
             let beforeId = null, closest = -Infinity;
             for (const el of rowEls) {
                 const box = el.getBoundingClientRect();
                 const offset = ev.clientY - box.top - box.height / 2;
                 if (offset < 0 && offset > closest) { closest = offset; beforeId = Number(el.dataset.rowId); }
             }
             this.rows = window.RecipeSections.placeRow(this.rows, this._dragId, section.heading, beforeId);
         },
         onDragEnd() {
             this._dragId = null;
             this._dragActive = false;
             this.rows = window.RecipeSections.normalizeRows(this.rows);         },
         removeTag(i) { this.tags.splice(i, 1); },
         selectProduct(row, detail) {
             row.productId = detail.value;
             row.productName = detail.name;
             row.isUntracked = detail.track === 'false';
             if (row.isUntracked) { row.qty = ''; row.unitId = ''; row.defaultUnitId = ''; row.defaultUnitCode = ''; }
             else if (detail.defaultUnit) { row.unitId = detail.defaultUnit; row.defaultUnitId = detail.defaultUnit; row.defaultUnitCode = detail.defaultUnitCode || ''; }
             // Clear any stale conversion prompt when the product changes.
             row.needsConversion = false; row.conversionFactor = '';
         },
         _convCheckTimer: null,
         _triggerConversionCheck() {
             clearTimeout(this._convCheckTimer);
             const draft = this.draft;
             if (draft.isUntracked) { draft.needsConversion = false; return; }

             // ── Inline-create path (plantry-dtr9) ────────────────────────────────────────
             // A create-view draft has no productId yet, so the product-scoped CheckConversion cannot run.
             // Compare the chosen recipe-line unit (draft.unitId) against the product default/stock unit
             // (draft.newStapleUnit) via the product-less CheckConversionUnits handler: a brand-new product
             // has zero ProductConversions, so same-dimension pairs bridge universally (no prompt) and only
             // a cross-dimension pair needs the four-field equation. Surfacing the prompt BEFORE save lets the
             // author supply the factor in-sheet, so the save carries it and Phase 3 resolves in one pass —
             // instead of bouncing and leaving an orphaned just-minted product. The prompt's stock-unit label
             // and product name are populated client-side (from newStapleUnit / newStapleName) since the
             // product does not exist yet; sibling plantry-obg3 owns the existing-product robustness.
             if (draft.newStapleName !== null && !draft.productId) {
                 if (!draft.unitId || !draft.newStapleUnit || draft.unitId === draft.newStapleUnit) {
                     draft.needsConversion = false;
                     return;
                 }
                 const stockUnitId = draft.newStapleUnit;
                 this._convCheckTimer = setTimeout(async () => {
                     const url = `@Url.Page("./Edit", "CheckConversionUnits")&defaultUnitId=${encodeURIComponent(stockUnitId)}&fromUnitId=${encodeURIComponent(draft.unitId)}`;
                     try {
                         const res = await fetch(url, { headers: { 'Accept': 'application/json' } });
                         if (!res.ok) return;
                         const data = await res.json();
                         if (data.needsConversion) {
                             draft.needsConversion = true;
                             // Product does not exist yet — label the ask from the in-progress draft.
                             if (!draft.productName) draft.productName = draft.newStapleName || '';
                             draft.defaultUnitId = data.defaultUnitId || stockUnitId;
                             draft.defaultUnitCode = data.defaultUnitCode || this.unitLabel(stockUnitId);
                             draft.stockUnits = data.stockUnits || [];
                             draft.recipeUnits = data.recipeUnits || [];
                             if (draft.convFor !== draft.unitId) {
                                 draft.convFor = draft.unitId;
                                 draft.convLeftAmount = '';
                                 draft.convRightAmount = '1';
                                 // plantry-dhqm: assign the axis unit ids AFTER the x-if prompt + x-for
                                 // options have rendered. Setting them in the same synchronous tick as
                                 // draft.stockUnits/recipeUnits let the select x-model push its value
                                 // before the matching option element existed, so the browser fell back to
                                 // the first option (e.g. cup, the alphabetically-first volume unit) while
                                 // the model still held the stock default (e.g. ml). The echo reads the
                                 // model, so the shown unit and the echoed unit disagreed until the author
                                 // re-picked. Awaiting $nextTick flushes the option render first so x-model
                                 // binds to a real option element. Capture the ids before the await so a
                                 // unit change landing mid-flush cannot skew the assignment. NB: no
                                 // double-quote character in this comment — it lives inside the x-data
                                 // attribute, so a stray quote would close it.
                                 const leftUnitId = draft.defaultUnitId, rightUnitId = draft.unitId;
                                 await this.$nextTick();
                                 draft.convLeftUnitId = leftUnitId;
                                 draft.convRightUnitId = rightUnitId;
                             }
                         } else {
                             draft.needsConversion = false;
                         }
                     } catch (_) { /* network error — server R7 backstop handles it */ }
                 }, 250);
                 return;
             }

             // ── Existing-product path (unchanged) ────────────────────────────────────────
             if (!draft.productId || !draft.unitId || draft.newStapleName !== null) {
                 draft.needsConversion = false;
                 return;
             }
             if (draft.unitId === draft.defaultUnitId) {
                 draft.needsConversion = false;
                 return;
             }
             this._convCheckTimer = setTimeout(async () => {
                 const url = `@Url.Page("./Edit", "CheckConversion")&productId=${encodeURIComponent(draft.productId)}&fromUnitId=${encodeURIComponent(draft.unitId)}`;
                 try {
                     const res = await fetch(url, { headers: { 'Accept': 'application/json' } });
                     if (!res.ok) return;
                     const data = await res.json();
                     if (data.needsConversion) {
                         draft.needsConversion = true;
                         // plantry-obg3/hhy2: an axis unit is unresolvable server-side — show the
                         // axis-appropriate explicit message instead of mounting the equation with a blank
                         // unit label and an option-less dropdown. Clear the axis lists so no stray options
                         // render. (!! guards older cached responses lacking the recipeUnitMissing field.)
                         if (data.defaultUnitMissing || data.recipeUnitMissing) {
                             draft.defaultUnitMissing = !!data.defaultUnitMissing;
                             draft.recipeUnitMissing = !!data.recipeUnitMissing;
                             draft.stockUnits = [];
                             draft.recipeUnits = [];
                             return;
                         }
                         draft.defaultUnitMissing = false;
                         draft.recipeUnitMissing = false;
                         draft.defaultUnitId = data.defaultUnitId || draft.defaultUnitId;
                         draft.defaultUnitCode = data.defaultUnitCode || draft.defaultUnitCode;
                         // Axis-locked unit lists for the four-field equation (plantry-qno9): LEFT lists
                         // stock-dimension units, RIGHT lists recipe-line-dimension units.
                         draft.stockUnits = data.stockUnits || [];
                         draft.recipeUnits = data.recipeUnits || [];
                         // Prefill the simplest one-number case (blank stock amount = 1 recipe unit).
                         // Only (re)prefill when the equation hasn't been built for THIS recipe-line unit yet
                         // (convFor tracks that) — so switching the recipe unit resets it, but merely
                         // re-opening a row (or a debounced re-check) preserves the author's in-progress entry.
                         if (draft.convFor !== draft.unitId) {
                             draft.convFor = draft.unitId;
                             draft.convLeftAmount = '';
                             draft.convRightAmount = '1';
                             // plantry-dhqm: assign the axis unit ids AFTER the x-if/x-for options render
                             // (see the inline-create path above for the full rationale) so the select
                             // x-model binds to a real option element instead of falling back to the first
                             // one while the model holds the stock default.
                             const leftUnitId = draft.defaultUnitId, rightUnitId = draft.unitId;
                             await this.$nextTick();
                             draft.convLeftUnitId = leftUnitId;
                             draft.convRightUnitId = rightUnitId;
                         }
                     } else {
                         draft.needsConversion = false;
                     }
                 } catch (_) { /* network error — silently ignore, server backstop handles it */ }
             }, 250);
         },
         showScaleOffer() { return !this.isCreate && (this.hasIngredients || this.rows.length > 0) && parseInt(this.servings) !== this.origServings; },
         isCreate: @(Model.IsCreate ? "true" : "false"),
         init() {
             this.$watch('draft.unitId', () => this._triggerConversionCheck());
             this.$watch('draft.productId', () => { this.draft.needsConversion = false; this._triggerConversionCheck(); });
             // plantry-dtr9: mirror the product default/stock unit into the recipe-line unit while the author
             // has not explicitly chosen a recipe unit (recipeUnitPinned) in the create view. Keeps the common
             // stock-it-in-the-unit-you-measure-in path one-tap AND makes the inherited value visible in the
             // create-view Unit select instead of silently applied at save (criterion 4). A user-chosen recipe
             // unit is pinned on select-change so it is never overwritten (criterion 3). Setting draft.unitId re-runs
             // the conversion check via its own watch; the else-branch covers the stock unit changing UNDER a
             // pinned recipe unit (the cross-dimension status may flip, so re-check).
             // NB: never use a double-quote character in an x-data comment — the whole initialiser lives inside
             // the x-data attribute, so a stray quote would close it. Every comment here uses plain words.
             this.$watch('draft.newStapleUnit', (val) => {
                 if (this.sheetView === 'create' && !this.draft.recipeUnitPinned) {
                     this.draft.unitId = val || '';
                 } else {
                     this._triggerConversionCheck();
                 }
             });
             // plantry-5oek: clear the sheet's tracked-quantity guard message whenever the view swaps
             // (search to/from create, incl. the partial's back-to-search / create-cancel backlinks).
             // NB: never use a double-quote character in an x-data comment — the whole initialiser lives
             // inside the x-data attribute, so a stray quote would close it. Every comment here uses plain
             // words for that reason.
             this.$watch('sheetView', (val, old) => {
                 this.sheetError = '';
                 // plantry-ts0a: leaving the create view abandons that product-create. The shared
                 // partial back-to-search / create-cancel handlers already null newStapleName and wipe
                 // newStapleUnit, but they cannot touch the Recipes-only recipeUnitPinned / unitId. Reset
                 // them here at the host level so the next fresh create mirrors the stock unit again
                 // (plantry-dtr9) instead of pre-filling the abandoned product unit. Guarded on
                 // old === create so ENTERING create (search to create, incl. openEdit reopen) never fires.
                 if (old === 'create' && val !== 'create') {
                     this.draft.recipeUnitPinned = false;
                     this.draft.unitId = '';
                 }
             });
         },
     }">

    @* ── Error banner ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── *@
    @if (Model.SaveError is { } err)
    {
        <div class="save-error" role="alert" style="background:var(--color-danger-bg);border:1px solid var(--color-danger);border-radius:var(--radius-md);padding:var(--space-3) var(--space-4);margin-bottom:var(--space-4);color:var(--color-danger)">
            <svg class="icon" aria-hidden="true"><use href="#i-alert" /></svg>
            @err
        </div>
    }

    <form method="post" enctype="multipart/form-data" class="form-stack">
        @Html.AntiForgeryToken()

        @* ── Recipe basics card ──────────────────────────────────────────────── *@
        <div class="card">
            <div class="card__head">
                <div><h3 class="card__head-title">Recipe details</h3></div>
            </div>
            <div class="card__body">
                <div class="form-grid">
                    <field asp-for="Input.Name" stacked full>
                        <input asp-for="Input.Name" class="field__input" placeholder="e.g. Chicken soup" />
                        <span asp-validation-for="Input.Name" class="field__error"></span>
                    </field>

                    <field asp-for="Input.DefaultServings" stacked label="Servings">
                        <input asp-for="Input.DefaultServings" class="field__input" type="number" min="1" step="1"
                               x-model.number="servings" />
                        <span asp-validation-for="Input.DefaultServings" class="field__error"></span>
                    </field>

                    <field asp-for="Input.CookTimeMinutes" stacked label="Cook Time">
                        <div class="form-grid__unit-suffix">
                            <input asp-for="Input.CookTimeMinutes" class="field__input" type="number" min="1" step="1" />
                            <span class="form-grid__unit-suffix__label">min</span>
                        </div>
                    </field>

                    <field asp-for="Input.Source" stacked full>
                        <input asp-for="Input.Source" class="field__input" placeholder="e.g. Family recipe or https://example.com/recipe" />
                    </field>

                    <div style="grid-column: 1 / -1">
                        <label class="form-grid__field__label" style="font-size:var(--font-size-sm);color:var(--color-text-muted);display:block;margin-bottom:var(--space-1)">Photo</label>
                        @if (!Model.IsCreate && Model.HasPhoto)
                        {
                            <a href="/Recipes/@Model.Id?handler=Photo" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
                               title="Open full image"
                               style="display:inline-block;margin-bottom:var(--space-2);border-radius:var(--radius-sm);overflow:hidden;border:1px solid var(--color-border);line-height:0">
                                <img src="/Recipes/@Model.Id?handler=Photo" alt="Current recipe photo" loading="lazy"
                                     style="display:block;width:120px;height:120px;object-fit:cover" />
                            </a>
                        }
                        <input type="file" name="photo" accept="image/*" class="field__input file-field" />
                        @if (!Model.IsCreate)
                        {
                            <p style="font-size:var(--font-size-sm);color:var(--color-text-muted);margin:var(--space-1) 0 0">Upload a new photo to replace the existing one. Leave blank to keep it.</p>
                        }
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        @* ── Yield-on-cook card (plantry-854a, recipe-composition.md §9) ───────── *@
        <div class="card" x-data="{ yieldOn: @(Model.Input.YieldEnabled ? "true" : "false") }">
            <div class="card__head">
                <div>
                    <h3 class="card__head-title">Yield (leftovers &amp; prepped stock)</h3>
                    <p class="card__head-sub">If cooking this makes stock you store and use later, declare it here — cooking will offer to add it to your pantry.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="card__body">
                <label style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:var(--space-2);cursor:pointer">
                    <input asp-for="Input.YieldEnabled" type="checkbox" x-model="yieldOn" />
                    <span>This recipe yields stored leftovers or prepped stock</span>
                </label>

                <div class="form-grid" x-show="yieldOn" x-cloak style="margin-top:var(--space-3)">
                    <field asp-for="Input.YieldQuantity" stacked label="Yield quantity">
                        <input asp-for="Input.YieldQuantity" class="field__input" type="number" min="0" step="0.001"
                               placeholder="e.g. 4" />
                        <span asp-validation-for="Input.YieldQuantity" class="field__error"></span>
                    </field>

                    <field asp-for="Input.YieldUnitId" stacked label="Yield unit">
                        <select asp-for="Input.YieldUnitId" asp-items="Model.UnitOptions" class="field__input">
                            <option value="">Choose a unit…</option>
                        </select>
                        <span asp-validation-for="Input.YieldUnitId" class="field__error"></span>
                    </field>
                </div>

                <p x-show="yieldOn" x-cloak style="margin-top:var(--space-2);font-size:var(--font-size-sm);color:var(--color-text-muted)">
                    A tracked product named after this recipe holds your stored stock. Use a count unit for servings, or a real unit (cups) for prep recipes.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        @* ── Servings scale offer (J7 step 3) — shown on edit when servings change ── *@
        @if (!Model.IsCreate)
        {
            <input type="hidden" name="Input.ScaleMode" :value="scaleMode" />
            <div class="card" x-show="showScaleOffer()" x-cloak>
                <div class="card__head">
                    <div>
                        <h3 class="card__head-title">Scale ingredients?</h3>
                        <p class="card__head-sub">You changed the default servings. How should ingredient quantities be adjusted?</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="card__body">
                    <div class="seg-ctrl" role="group" aria-label="Scale mode">
                        <label class="seg-ctrl__item">
                            <input type="radio" name="_scaleMode" value="Proportional" x-model="scaleMode" />
                            <span>Proportional — scale quantities</span>
                        </label>
                        <label class="seg-ctrl__item">
                            <input type="radio" name="_scaleMode" value="Keep" x-model="scaleMode" />
                            <span>Keep — preserve quantities</span>
                        </label>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        }
        else
        {
            <input type="hidden" name="Input.ScaleMode" value="Keep" />
        }

        @* ── D13 fixed-mode warning (plantry-fqb0.3) — this recipe is included by others; changing its
              servings in Keep (fixed) mode silently changes what a serving means for its includers. Shown
              only in edit mode, when the recipe has includers, servings drifted, and Keep is selected. ── *@
        @if (!Model.IsCreate)
        {
            <div class="card"
                 x-show="includedByCount > 0 && parseInt(servings) !== origServings && scaleMode === 'Keep'"
                 x-cloak
                 style="border-color:var(--color-warning)">
                <div class="card__body" style="display:flex;gap:var(--space-3);align-items:flex-start">
                    <svg class="icon" aria-hidden="true" style="color:var(--color-warning);flex-shrink:0;margin-top:2px"><use href="#i-alert" /></svg>
                    <div>
                        <p style="margin:0 0 var(--space-1);font-weight:600">Changing servings affects other recipes</p>
                        <p style="margin:0;font-size:var(--font-size-sm);color:var(--color-text-muted)">
                            Keeping quantities while changing the serving count changes what one serving means for
                            <span x-text="includedByLabel()"></span>. Choose <strong>Proportional</strong> above to scale them together, or continue if that is intended.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        }

        @* ── Tags type-to-filter multi-select (read-only vocabulary) ──────────── *@
        @* card--overflow-visible: the tag picker dropdown is position:absolute inside the
           card body; without it the dropdown is clipped at the card's overflow:hidden edge. *@
        <div class="card card--overflow-visible">
            <div class="card__head">
                <div>
                    <h3 class="card__head-title">Tags</h3>
                    <p class="card__head-sub">Type to filter defined tags and select one to add it as a chip.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="card__body">
                @* Hidden inputs post the selected TagIds array (one input per chip) *@
                <template x-for="(tag, ti) in tags" :key="tag.id">
                    <input type="hidden" name="Input.TagIds" :value="tag.id" />
                </template>

                @* Accepted AI new-tag chips (plantry-qll2.2) — minted on save then applied. Indexed hidden
                   inputs so the page model binds Input.NewTags[i].Name / .Category. *@
                <template x-for="(nt, ni) in newTags" :key="'newtag-' + ni">
                    <span>
                        <input type="hidden" :name="'Input.NewTags[' + ni + '].Name'" :value="nt.name" />
                        <input type="hidden" :name="'Input.NewTags[' + ni + '].Category'" :value="nt.category" />
                    </span>
                </template>

                @* Empty-household guidance: shown when no active tags are defined *@
                @if (!Model.TagOptions.Any())
                {
                    <p style="font-size:var(--font-size-sm);color:var(--color-text-muted)">
                        No tags defined yet.
                        <a href="/Settings/Tags">Manage tags in Settings</a> to build your vocabulary.
                    </p>
                }
                else
                {
                    @* Chip display + filter input with dropdown ──────────────────── *@
                    @* click.outside lives on this wrapper (spans input + dropdown) so a mouse
                       focus-click on the input is "inside" and never closes the just-opened list. *@
                    <div style="position:relative" @@click.outside="tagDropOpen = false">
                        <div class="recipe-tag-editor" style="display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:var(--space-2);align-items:center;border:1px solid var(--color-border);border-radius:var(--radius-md);padding:var(--space-2) var(--space-3);min-height:2.5rem;cursor:text" @@click="$refs.tagInput.focus()">
                            <template x-for="(tag, ti) in tags" :key="tag.id">
                                <span class="badge badge--neutral" style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:var(--space-1)">
                                    <span x-text="tag.name"></span>
                                    <button type="button" class="btn btn--ghost btn--sm" style="padding:0 2px;line-height:1;font-size:inherit" aria-label="Remove tag" @@click.stop="removeTag(ti)">×</button>
                                </span>
                            </template>
                            @* Accepted new-tag chips (plantry-qll2.2) — visually flagged 'new' until minted on save. *@
                            <template x-for="(nt, ni) in newTags" :key="'newchip-' + ni">
                                <span class="badge badge--neutral" style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:var(--space-1)">
                                    <span x-text="nt.name"></span>
                                    <span class="ai-chip__new-hint">new tag</span>
                                    <button type="button" class="btn btn--ghost btn--sm" style="padding:0 2px;line-height:1;font-size:inherit" aria-label="Remove tag" @@click.stop="removeNewTag(ni)">×</button>
                                </span>
                            </template>
                            <input type="text" x-ref="tagInput" x-model="tagQuery"
                                   placeholder="Filter tags…"
                                   class="field__input" style="border:none;outline:none;box-shadow:none;padding:0;min-width:8rem;flex:1"
                                   @@focus="tagDropOpen = true"
                                   @@input="tagDropOpen = true"
                                   @@keydown.escape="tagDropOpen = false; tagQuery = ''"
                                   @@keydown.backspace="if (!tagQuery && tags.length) removeTag(tags.length - 1)"
                                   autocomplete="off" />
                        </div>
                        @* Dropdown — lists matching active tags not already selected *@
                        <div x-show="tagDropOpen && filteredTagOptions().length > 0"
                             x-cloak
                             style="position:absolute;z-index:50;left:0;right:0;margin-top:2px;background:var(--color-surface);border:1px solid var(--color-border);border-radius:var(--radius-md);max-height:12rem;overflow-y:auto;box-shadow:var(--shadow-md)">
                            <template x-for="opt in filteredTagOptions()" :key="opt.id">
                                <button type="button"
                                        class="tag-picker-option"
                                        style="display:block;width:100%;text-align:left;padding:var(--space-2) var(--space-3);background:none;border:none;cursor:pointer;font:inherit;color:var(--color-text)"
                                        @@mousedown.prevent="addTagFromOption(opt)"
                                        x-text="opt.name"></button>
                            </template>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    @* ── AI tag suggestions row (plantry-qll2.2) ─────────────────────
                       Sits directly under the tag editor. Populated once per create when the first
                       ingredient is added (maybeSuggestTags); renders nothing when there are no
                       suggestions or the user dismissed them (no empty-state noise). Each chip applies
                       ONLY on tap — never auto-applied. Dashed .ai-chip--new chips would mint a new tag. *@
                    <div x-cloak x-show="tagSuggestions.length > 0 && !tagSuggestDismissed" class="ai-suggest-row">
                        <div class="ai-suggest-row__label">
                            <span aria-hidden="true">✨</span>
                            <span>Suggested from ingredients</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="ai-suggest-row__chips">
                            <template x-for="sug in tagSuggestions" :key="(sug.isNew ? 'new:' : 'tag:') + sug.name">
                                <button type="button"
                                        class="ai-chip"
                                        :class="{ 'ai-chip--new': sug.isNew }"
                                        @@click="acceptSuggestion(sug)">
                                    <span aria-hidden="true">＋</span>
                                    <span x-text="sug.name"></span>
                                    <span class="ai-chip__new-hint" x-show="sug.isNew">new tag</span>
                                </button>
                            </template>
                            <button type="button" class="btn btn--ghost btn--sm ai-suggest-row__dismiss"
                                    @@click="dismissSuggestions()">Dismiss</button>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                }
            </div>
        </div>

        @* ── Ingredients ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────── *@
        @* card--overflow-visible: the 'Include a recipe' search dropdown is position:absolute
           inside this card; without it the dropdown is clipped at the card's overflow:hidden edge. *@
        <div class="card card--overflow-visible">
            <div class="card__head">
                <div>
                    <h3 class="card__head-title">Ingredients</h3>
                    <p class="card__head-sub">Group into sections like “For the sauce” — set an ingredient’s <strong>Section</strong> in its add/edit form to start one. Drag a row to reorder it, or across a section to move it. Rename a section heading once to rename it for every ingredient in it.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="card__body" style="padding:0">
                @*
                    Hidden form inputs — the source of truth that POSTs. Rendered from the flat, canonical
                    `rows` array (index 0..n-1) so Input.Lines[i] binds in the same order Details will
                    group and render (recipe-sections.js keeps rows ungrouped-first + sections first-seen
                    with ordinal == index). Kept separate from the sectioned visual below so the visual
                    can cluster rows without disturbing the posted index/ordinal. The row objects here are
                    the SAME references the visual renders, so edits (e.g. the conversion factor) sync.
                *@
                <div hidden aria-hidden="true">
                    <template x-for="(row, idx) in ingredientRows()" :key="row._id">
                        <div>
                            <input type="hidden" :name="'Input.Lines[' + idx + '].Ordinal'" :value="row.ordinal" />
                            <input type="hidden" :name="'Input.Lines[' + idx + '].ProductId'" :value="row.productId" />
                            @* ProductName is display-only but must be posted so the re-rendered form
                               can repopulate the Alpine productName state after a validation failure. *@
                            <input type="hidden" :name="'Input.Lines[' + idx + '].ProductName'" :value="row.productName" />
                            <input type="hidden" :name="'Input.Lines[' + idx + '].NewStapleName'" :value="row.newStapleName ?? ''" />
                            <input type="hidden" :name="'Input.Lines[' + idx + '].NewStapleDefaultUnitId'" :value="row.newStapleUnit" />
                            @* Tracked-product create fields (plantry-orix) *@
                            <input type="hidden" :name="'Input.Lines[' + idx + '].NewIsTracked'" :value="row.newIsTracked" />
                            <input type="hidden" :name="'Input.Lines[' + idx + '].NewGroupId'" :value="row.newGroupId ?? ''" />
                            <input type="hidden" :name="'Input.Lines[' + idx + '].NewGroupName'" :value="row.newGroupName ?? ''" />
                            <input type="hidden" :name="'Input.Lines[' + idx + '].NewStapleCategoryId'" :value="row.newStapleCategoryId ?? ''" />
                            <input type="hidden" :name="'Input.Lines[' + idx + '].Quantity'" :value="row.qty" />
                            <input type="hidden" :name="'Input.Lines[' + idx + '].UnitId'" :value="row.unitId" />
                            @* IsUntracked round-trips the real per-line tracked state so a failed-save
                               re-render keeps the correct row warnings/summary (plantry-429l). Display-only:
                               AuthorRecipe re-resolves TrackStock from the product, never trusting this. *@
                            <input type="hidden" :name="'Input.Lines[' + idx + '].IsUntracked'" :value="row.isUntracked" />
                            <input type="hidden" :name="'Input.Lines[' + idx + '].GroupHeading'" :value="row.groupHeading" />
                            <input type="hidden" :name="'Input.Lines[' + idx + '].ConversionFactor'" :value="row.conversionFactor" />
                            @* Four-field equation (plantry-qno9): the server computes factor = right/left,
                               from = left unit, to = right unit. These carry the raw author entry. *@
                            <input type="hidden" :name="'Input.Lines[' + idx + '].ConversionLeftAmount'" :value="row.convLeftAmount" />
                            <input type="hidden" :name="'Input.Lines[' + idx + '].ConversionLeftUnitId'" :value="row.convLeftUnitId" />
                            <input type="hidden" :name="'Input.Lines[' + idx + '].ConversionRightAmount'" :value="row.convRightAmount" />
                            <input type="hidden" :name="'Input.Lines[' + idx + '].ConversionRightUnitId'" :value="row.convRightUnitId" />
                        </div>
                    </template>
                    @* Inclusion rows (plantry-fqb0.3) post their own contiguous-index block; each carries the
                       SHARED `ordinal` so AuthorRecipe interleaves them with the ingredient lines (N3). *@
                    <template x-for="(inc, jdx) in inclusionRows()" :key="inc._id">
                        <div>
                            <input type="hidden" :name="'Input.Inclusions[' + jdx + '].Ordinal'" :value="inc.ordinal" />
                            <input type="hidden" :name="'Input.Inclusions[' + jdx + '].SubRecipeId'" :value="inc.subRecipeId" />
                            <input type="hidden" :name="'Input.Inclusions[' + jdx + '].SubName'" :value="inc.subName" />
                            <input type="hidden" :name="'Input.Inclusions[' + jdx + '].Servings'" :value="inc.servings" />
                            <input type="hidden" :name="'Input.Inclusions[' + jdx + '].SubDefaultServings'" :value="inc.subDefaultServings" />
                            <input type="hidden" :name="'Input.Inclusions[' + jdx + '].GroupHeading'" :value="inc.groupHeading" />
                        </div>
                    </template>
                </div>

                @* Sectioned, drag-reorderable ingredient list — mirrors the Details grouping. *@
                <div id="ingredient-rows" :class="{ 'ingredient-sections--dragging': _dragActive }">
                    <template x-for="section in sections()" :key="section.key">
                        @* Whole section is a drop zone: dragging over its header or its rows moves the
                           dragged row into it (reassigning group), live-shifting to the cursor position. *@
                        <div class="ing-section"
                             @@dragover.prevent="onDragOver(section, $event)"
                             @@drop.prevent="onDragEnd()">

                            @* Named-section header: inline rename + count + delete. Ungrouped header is
                               nameless/muted and only shown once a named section exists. *@
                            <div class="ing-section__head" x-show="!section.isUngrouped || showUngroupedHeader()">
                                <template x-if="section.isUngrouped">
                                    <span class="ing-section__name ing-section__name--ungrouped" title="Ingredients with no section">Ungrouped</span>
                                </template>
                                <template x-if="!section.isUngrouped">
                                    <input class="ing-section__name" type="text"
                                           :value="section.heading"
                                           title="Rename this section — every ingredient in it follows"
                                           aria-label="Section heading"
                                           @@change="renameSection(section.heading, $event.target.value)"
                                           @@keydown.enter.prevent="$event.target.blur()" />
                                </template>
                                <span class="ing-section__count"
                                      x-text="section.items.length + (section.items.length === 1 ? ' item' : ' items')"></span>
                                <template x-if="!section.isUngrouped">
                                    <button type="button" class="ing-section__del"
                                            aria-label="Delete section"
                                            title="Delete section (its ingredients move to Ungrouped)"
                                            @@click="deleteSection(section.heading)">
                                        <svg class="icon" aria-hidden="true"><use href="#i-minus" /></svg>
                                    </button>
                                </template>
                            </div>

                            <div class="ing-rows">
                                <template x-for="row in section.items" :key="row._id">
                                    <div class="ingredient-row"
                                         :data-row-id="row._id"
                                         :class="{ 'ingredient-row--needs-conversion': row.needsConversion && !rowConvFilled(row), 'ingredient-row--needs-attention': rowNeedsQtyUnit(row), 'ingredient-row--dragging': row._id === _dragId }"
                                         draggable="true"
                                         @@dragstart="onDragStart(row, $event)"
                                         @@dragend="onDragEnd()">

                                        @* ── Inclusion row body (plantry-fqb0.3) — 'N servings · Sub' + batch hint,
                                              inline decimal servings stepper, remove. Shares drag/section/ordinal
                                              behaviour with ingredient rows via the shared rows[] model. ── *@
                                        <template x-if="row.kind === 'inclusion'">
                                            <div class="ingredient-row__body">
                                                <div class="ingredient-row__drag" aria-hidden="true" title="Drag to reorder or move between sections">
                                                    <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"><line x1="3" y1="8" x2="21" y2="8"/><line x1="3" y1="16" x2="21" y2="16"/></svg>
                                                </div>
                                                <div class="incl-row__main">
                                                    <div class="incl-row__title">
                                                        <svg class="icon" aria-hidden="true"><use href="#i-recipe" /></svg>
                                                        <span x-text="inclusionServingsLabel(row) + ' · ' + row.subName"></span>
                                                    </div>
                                                    <div class="incl-row__hint" x-show="batchHint(row)" x-cloak x-text="'≈ ' + batchHint(row)"></div>
                                                </div>
                                                <label class="incl-row__servings">
                                                    <span class="incl-row__servings-lbl">Servings</span>
                                                    <input type="number" min="0.25" step="0.25"
                                                           class="field__input incl-row__servings-input"
                                                           aria-label="Servings of the included recipe"
                                                           x-model.number="row.servings" />
                                                </label>
                                                <button type="button" class="btn btn--ghost btn--sm ingredient-row__action"
                                                        aria-label="Remove included recipe" @@click="removeRow(row)"
                                                        style="color:var(--color-danger)">
                                                    <svg class="icon" aria-hidden="true"><use href="#i-minus" /></svg>
                                                </button>
                                            </div>
                                        </template>

                                        @* ── Ingredient row body ── *@
                                        <template x-if="row.kind !== 'inclusion'">
                                        <div class="ingredient-row__body">
                                            @* Drag handle *@
                                            <div class="ingredient-row__drag" aria-hidden="true" title="Drag to reorder or move between sections">
                                                <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"><line x1="3" y1="8" x2="21" y2="8"/><line x1="3" y1="16" x2="21" y2="16"/></svg>
                                            </div>

                                            @* Summary — product · qty unit. Click to edit. *@
                                            <button type="button" class="ingredient-row__summary"
                                                    @@click="openEdit(row)"
                                                    :title="'Edit ' + (row.newStapleName || row.productName)">
                                                <span x-text="rowSummary(row)"></span>
                                            </button>

                                            @* Edit *@
                                            <button type="button" class="btn btn--ghost btn--sm ingredient-row__action"
                                                    aria-label="Edit ingredient" @@click="openEdit(row)">
                                                <svg class="icon" aria-hidden="true"><use href="#i-edit" /></svg>
                                            </button>
                                            @* Delete *@
                                            <button type="button" class="btn btn--ghost btn--sm ingredient-row__action"
                                                    aria-label="Remove ingredient" @@click="removeRow(row)"
                                                    style="color:var(--color-danger)">
                                                <svg class="icon" aria-hidden="true"><use href="#i-minus" /></svg>
                                            </button>
                                        </div>
                                        </template>

                                        @* Row-scoped "tracked needs qty + unit" warning (plantry-429l).
                                           Surfaces the R5 dead-end at the offending row — a row authored
                                           while untracked whose product was later flipped tracked — instead
                                           of only the opaque global save banner. Reuses the conversion
                                           path's warning styling. Clears reactively once qty is supplied. *@
                                        <div x-show="rowNeedsQtyUnit(row)"
                                             class="ingredient-row__needs-qty"
                                             style="background:var(--color-warning-bg);border-top:1px solid var(--color-warning);padding:var(--space-3) var(--space-4)">
                                            <p style="font-size:var(--font-size-sm);margin:0;display:flex;align-items:center;gap:var(--space-2);color:var(--color-text)">
                                                <svg class="icon" aria-hidden="true"><use href="#i-alert" /></svg>
                                                <span>This ingredient is now stock-tracked and needs a quantity and unit.</span>
                                                <button type="button" class="btn btn--ghost btn--sm" @@click="openEdit(row)">Add quantity</button>
                                            </p>
                                        </div>

                                        @* Landed-row conversion block (plantry-wq9s) — the four-field equation
                                           editor (plantry-qno9) with two tones. FILLED = neutral confirmation of
                                           a conversion the author already stated (echo + saved-on-save note, no
                                           warning); MISSING = warning-accented informational ask in the in-sheet
                                           voice so a bounced/skipped save is findable and fixable inline. The four
                                           inputs bind the same row.conv* fields that post via the hidden inputs
                                           below, and match _IngredientConversionPrompt.cshtml's framing. *@
                                        @* GUARD-RAIL (plantry-kw1t): the FILLED/MISSING tone is a :class toggle, NOT a
                                           string :style. This element also carries x-show; Alpine applies a string :style by
                                           rewriting the whole style attribute, wiping x-show's display:none — and x-show's
                                           cached _x_isShown then skips re-hiding, leaving a phantom conversion prompt shown.
                                           :class never touches the style attribute, so x-show's hidden state survives.
                                           Never bind a string :style on an element that also has x-show. *@
                                        <div x-show="rowShowConversion(row)"
                                             x-init="maybeHydrateRowConversion(row)"
                                             class="ingredient-row__conversion"
                                             :class="rowConvFilled(row)
                                                ? 'ingredient-row__conversion--filled'
                                                : 'ingredient-row__conversion--missing'">
                                            @* plantry-obg3: product has no resolvable stock/default unit
                                               (unset or dangling DefaultUnitId). Show an explicit, actionable
                                               message instead of the blank-unit sentence + option-less
                                               equation — mirrors _IngredientConversionPrompt.cshtml. When BOTH
                                               axes are missing this stock copy wins (it carries the actionable
                                               remedy) — see the !defaultUnitMissing prefix on the recipe branch. *@
                                            <p x-show="row.defaultUnitMissing" x-cloak
                                               style="font-size:var(--font-size-sm);margin:0;display:flex;align-items:flex-start;gap:var(--space-2);color:var(--color-text)">
                                                <svg class="icon" aria-hidden="true" style="flex:none"><use href="#i-alert" /></svg>
                                                <span>
                                                    <strong x-text="row.productName"></strong> has no stock unit set, so Plantry can't
                                                    work out the conversion. Set a default unit for this product in your catalog first.
                                                </span>
                                            </p>

                                            @* plantry-hhy2: the RIGHT/recipe-axis unit chosen for this line is
                                               unresolvable (dangling/deleted unit) while the stock axis is fine.
                                               Recipe-axis copy — no remedy about the catalog default unit, and no
                                               unitLabel() (the unresolvable unit has no code to show). Suppressed
                                               when defaultUnitMissing so the stock copy takes precedence. *@
                                            <p x-show="!row.defaultUnitMissing && row.recipeUnitMissing" x-cloak
                                               style="font-size:var(--font-size-sm);margin:0;display:flex;align-items:flex-start;gap:var(--space-2);color:var(--color-text)">
                                                <svg class="icon" aria-hidden="true" style="flex:none"><use href="#i-alert" /></svg>
                                                <span>
                                                    The unit chosen for <strong x-text="row.productName"></strong> on this recipe line can't
                                                    be resolved, so Plantry can't work out the conversion. Pick a different unit for this ingredient.
                                                </span>
                                            </p>

                                            @* MISSING — informational ask (same wording family as the in-sheet prompt) *@
                                            <p x-show="!rowConvFilled(row) && !row.defaultUnitMissing && !row.recipeUnitMissing"
                                               style="font-size:var(--font-size-sm);margin:0 0 var(--space-2)">
                                                Plantry stocks <strong x-text="row.productName"></strong> in <strong x-text="row.defaultUnitCode"></strong>.
                                                How does 1 <span x-text="unitLabel(row.unitId)"></span> relate?
                                            </p>

                                            @* Two-sided equation (LEFT stock dimension = RIGHT recipe-line dimension),
                                               each select axis-locked, + the FILLED derived-echo line — shared partial
                                               (plantry-pqlo). The saved-on-save note below stays here (row-specific).
                                               Suppressed entirely when either axis unit is unresolvable
                                               (plantry-obg3/hhy2) so the option-less dropdown is unreachable. *@
                                            <template x-if="!row.defaultUnitMissing && !row.recipeUnitMissing">
                                                @* Single wrapper root: the equation partial renders two
                                                   sibling elements (.conv-eq + echo <p>), but Alpine x-if
                                                   needs one root — so wrap them. *@
                                                <div>
                                                    <partial name="Shared/_ConversionEquation"
                                                             model='new Plantry.Web.Pages.Shared.ConversionEquationViewModel
                                                             {
                                                                 Root              = "row",
                                                                 EchoExpression    = "rowConversionEcho(row)",
                                                                 EchoShowExpression = "rowConvFilled(row)",
                                                             }' />
                                                </div>
                                            </template>

                                            @* FILLED — saved-on-save note (row-specific), neutral tone *@
                                            <p x-show="rowConvFilled(row)" x-cloak
                                               style="margin:var(--space-1) 0 0;font-size:var(--font-size-sm);color:var(--color-text-muted)">
                                                Saved to your catalog when you save the recipe.
                                            </p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </template>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </template>
                </div>

                @* Empty state *@
                <div x-show="rows.length === 0"
                     style="padding:var(--space-4);color:var(--color-text-muted);font-size:var(--font-size-sm)">
                    No ingredients yet — add your first one below.
                </div>

                <div style="padding:var(--space-4);display:flex;gap:var(--space-2);flex-wrap:wrap;align-items:flex-start">
                    <button type="button" class="btn btn--ghost btn--sm" @@click="openAdd()">
                        <svg class="icon" aria-hidden="true"><use href="#i-plus" /></svg>
                        Add ingredient
                    </button>

                    @* ── Include a recipe (plantry-fqb0.3, D11) — recipe-search dropdown. Self is excluded
                          server-side (N4 authoritative at save); duplicate subs are allowed (D14). ── *@
                    <div class="incl-search-wrap" style="position:relative">
                        <button type="button" class="btn btn--ghost btn--sm" @@click="openInclusionSearch()">
                            <svg class="icon" aria-hidden="true"><use href="#i-plus" /></svg>
                            Include a recipe
                        </button>
                        <div x-show="inclusionSearchOpen" x-cloak
                             @@click.outside="closeInclusionSearch()"
                             class="incl-search">
                            <input type="text" x-ref="inclusionInput" x-model="inclusionQuery"
                                   @@input="searchInclusions()"
                                   @@keydown.escape="closeInclusionSearch()"
                                   placeholder="Search your recipes…"
                                   class="field__input" autocomplete="off" />
                            <div class="incl-search__results">
                                <template x-if="inclusionResults.length === 0">
                                    <p class="incl-search__empty" x-text="inclusionQuery.trim() ? 'No matching recipes.' : 'Type to search your recipes.'"></p>
                                </template>
                                <template x-for="hit in inclusionResults" :key="hit.id">
                                    <button type="button" class="incl-search__opt" @@click="addInclusion(hit)">
                                        <span class="incl-search__opt-name" x-text="hit.name"></span>
                                        <span class="incl-search__opt-meta"
                                              x-text="hit.defaultServings + (hit.defaultServings === 1 ? ' serving' : ' servings')"></span>
                                    </button>
                                </template>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        @* ── Ingredient add/edit sheet (P4-6: shared partial) ──────────────────────── *@
        @* Kept in the DOM via x-show (not x-if) so the searchable-select Alpine component inits
           once at page load — see _ProductSearchCreateSheet.cshtml for the rationale. *@
        @*
            GroupOptions and CategoryOptions are populated by the page model (plantry-orix) so the
            create-view Group combobox (plantry-40n6) and Defaults collapsible (plantry-y53t) render
            with the household's real data. CreateLabel is "as a new product" (not the Recipes default
            "as a new staple") because the create view now mints a tracked catalog product —
            the untracked-staple path (C12) still works via the legacy newIsTracked=false route.
        *@
        <partial name="Shared/_ProductSearchCreateSheet"
                 model='new Plantry.Web.Pages.Shared.ProductSearchCreateSheetViewModel
                 {
                     SearchUrl           = Url.Page("./Edit", "SearchProducts")!,
                     UnitOptions         = Model.UnitOptions,
                     CategoryOptions     = Model.CategoryOptions,
                     GroupOptions        = Model.GroupOptions,
                     TrackStock          = true,
                     ExtraFieldsPartial  = "Shared/_IngredientConversionPrompt",
                     CreateLabel         = "as a new product",
                     StapleNamePlaceholder = "Product name (e.g. Olive Oil)",
                 }' />

        @* ── Directions ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────── *@
        <div class="card">
            <div class="card__head">
                <div>
                    <h3 class="card__head-title">Directions</h3>
                    <p class="card__head-sub">One step per line. A blank line starts a new step. A line starting with # becomes a section heading.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="card__body">
                <textarea asp-for="Input.Directions"
                          class="field__input"
                          rows="10"
                          placeholder="# Prep&#10;Dice the onion.&#10;&#10;Sauté in butter for 5 minutes.&#10;&#10;# Cook&#10;Add the broth and simmer 20 minutes."
                          style="width:100%;resize:vertical;font-family:inherit"></textarea>
            </div>
        </div>

        @* ── Submit bar ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────── *@
        @* commit-bar--flow: render in normal flow at the form foot, not sticky (plantry-f7uk).
           The sticky variant pinned to the viewport bottom and floated over the Ingredients card
           on a form taller than the viewport, partially hiding it. *@
        <div class="commit-bar commit-bar--flow">
            <a href="@(Model.IsCreate ? "/Recipes" : $"/Recipes/{Model.Id}")" class="btn btn--ghost commit-bar__cancel">Cancel</a>
            <span class="commit-bar__spacer"></span>
            <button type="submit" class="btn btn--primary">
                @(Model.IsCreate ? "Create Recipe" : "Save changes")
            </button>
        </div>
    </form>
</div>

@* ── CSS for ingredient sections + rows (scoped to this page) ─────────────────── *@
<style>
    /* ── Section (plantry-vff8): heading card + its clustered rows ── */
    .ing-section { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
    .ing-section:last-of-type { border-bottom: none; }
    .ing-section__head {
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: var(--space-2);
        padding: var(--space-3) var(--space-3) var(--space-2) var(--space-4);
    }
    .ing-section__name {
        flex: 1;
        min-width: 0;
        font-size: 11px;
        letter-spacing: .06em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--color-text-faint);
        font-weight: 700;
        background: none;
        border: 1px solid transparent;
        border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
        padding: 3px 6px;
        font-family: inherit;
    }
    /* Only the editable (named) heading gets the hover/focus affordance. */
    input.ing-section__name:hover { border-color: var(--color-border); }
    input.ing-section__name:focus {
        outline: none;
        border-color: var(--color-accent);
        background: var(--color-surface-2);
        color: var(--color-text);
        letter-spacing: normal;
        text-transform: none;
        font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
        font-weight: 600;
    }
    .ing-section__name--ungrouped { font-style: italic; color: var(--color-text-faint); }
    .ing-section__count { font-size: 11px; color: var(--color-text-faint); font-weight: 600; flex-shrink: 0; }
    .ing-section__del {
        background: none;
        border: none;
        color: var(--color-text-faint);
        cursor: pointer;
        padding: 4px;
        border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
        flex-shrink: 0;
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
    }
    .ing-section__del:hover { color: var(--color-danger); background: var(--color-danger-bg); }

    .ing-rows { min-height: 4px; }
    /* While a drag is active, keep even an emptied section a comfortable drop target. */
    .ingredient-sections--dragging .ing-rows { min-height: 34px; }

    .ingredient-row {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    }
    .ing-rows .ingredient-row:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
    .ingredient-row--needs-conversion { border-left: 3px solid var(--color-warning); }
    /* plantry-429l: tracked row missing qty/unit — same warning accent as the conversion path. */
    .ingredient-row--needs-attention { border-left: 3px solid var(--color-warning); }
    .ingredient-row--dragging { opacity: .4; }

    /* Landed-row conversion block tones (plantry-kw1t). The FILLED/MISSING tone MUST be
       carried by :class modifiers, NOT a string :style ternary. This element also has x-show,
       and Alpine applies a string :style by rewriting the element's entire style attribute —
       which erases the display:none that x-show set. Because x-show caches _x_isShown, it then
       skips re-hiding and the block stays visibly shown (the phantom conversion prompt). :class
       toggles never touch the style attribute, so x-show's hidden state survives.
       GUARD-RAIL: never bind a string :style on an element that also carries x-show. */
    .ingredient-row__conversion { padding: var(--space-3) var(--space-4); }
    .ingredient-row__conversion--filled  { background: var(--color-surface-2);   border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
    .ingredient-row__conversion--missing { background: var(--color-warning-bg);  border-top: 1px solid var(--color-warning); }

    /* Read-only landed row: drag · summary (grows) · edit · delete */
    .ingredient-row__body {
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: var(--space-2);
        padding: var(--space-2) var(--space-3) var(--space-2) var(--space-4);
    }
    .ingredient-row__drag {
        cursor: grab;
        color: var(--color-text-muted);
        padding: var(--space-2);
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        flex-shrink: 0;
    }
    /* Summary reads as text but is a button (click-to-edit). */
    .ingredient-row__summary {
        flex: 1;
        min-width: 0;
        text-align: left;
        background: none;
        border: none;
        padding: var(--space-2) 0;
        font: inherit;
        color: var(--color-text);
        cursor: pointer;
    }
    .ingredient-row__summary:hover { color: var(--color-accent); }
    .ingredient-row__action { flex-shrink: 0; }

    .recipe-tag-editor:focus-within { border-color: var(--color-accent); }
    .tag-picker-option:hover { background: var(--color-surface-2) !important; }

    /* AI tag-suggestion row (plantry-qll2.2) — sits under the tag editor. Page-specific layout that
       composes the shared .ai-chip primitive (defined in plenish.css). */
    .ai-suggest-row { margin-top: var(--space-3); }
    .ai-suggest-row__label {
        display: flex; align-items: center; gap: var(--space-1);
        font-family: var(--font-mono, var(--font-sans));
        font-size: var(--font-size-xs);
        text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.04em;
        color: var(--color-text-muted);
        margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
    }
    .ai-suggest-row__chips { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: var(--space-2); align-items: center; }
    .ai-suggest-row__dismiss { color: var(--color-text-muted); }

    /* ── Inclusion rows (plantry-fqb0.3): 'N servings · Sub' + batch hint + inline servings stepper ── */
    .incl-row__main { flex: 1; min-width: 0; padding: var(--space-2) 0; }
    .incl-row__title { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: var(--space-2); color: var(--color-text); }
    .incl-row__title .icon { color: var(--color-accent); flex-shrink: 0; }
    .incl-row__hint { font-size: var(--font-size-sm); color: var(--color-text-muted); margin-top: 2px; }
    .incl-row__servings { display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: flex-end; gap: 2px; flex-shrink: 0; }
    .incl-row__servings-lbl { font-size: 11px; color: var(--color-text-faint); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: .06em; font-weight: 600; }
    .incl-row__servings-input { width: 5rem; text-align: right; }

    /* Include-a-recipe search dropdown */
    .incl-search {
        position: absolute; z-index: 50; left: 0; top: calc(100% + 4px);
        width: 20rem; max-width: 90vw;
        background: var(--color-surface); border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
        border-radius: var(--radius-md); box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);
        padding: var(--space-2);
    }
    .incl-search__results { margin-top: var(--space-2); max-height: 14rem; overflow-y: auto; }
    .incl-search__empty { font-size: var(--font-size-sm); color: var(--color-text-muted); padding: var(--space-2); margin: 0; }
    .incl-search__opt {
        display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; gap: var(--space-2);
        width: 100%; text-align: left; background: none; border: none; cursor: pointer;
        padding: var(--space-2) var(--space-3); font: inherit; color: var(--color-text);
        border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    }
    .incl-search__opt:hover { background: var(--color-surface-2); }
    .incl-search__opt-name { min-width: 0; overflow: hidden; text-overflow: ellipsis; white-space: nowrap; }
    .incl-search__opt-meta { font-size: var(--font-size-sm); color: var(--color-text-faint); flex-shrink: 0; }
</style>

@section Scripts {
    @* Bridge the pure section-transform module onto window.RecipeSections. Loads after Alpine
       starts; every handler that calls it (drag, rename, delete, add, remove) runs at interaction
       time, so it is guaranteed present by then. Not an island — no reactive runtime here. *@
    <script type="module">
        window.RecipeSections = await import('@Html.Raw(recipeSectionsSrc)');
        window.IngredientAmount = await import('@Html.Raw(ingredientAmountSrc)');
        window.IngredientConversion = await import('@Html.Raw(ingredientConversionSrc)');
    </script>
}
